column14: @ Uncertainty: IVE method, 2-sigma value (2 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.ft File). @ THE DWL FROM YESTERDAY'S VISIT WAS MISTAKENLY RUN FROM BM 02-1, WHICH IS LOCATED A FEW METRE'S AWAY FROM HOLDING (BM 00-1) ON THE SAME BRIDGE STRUCTURE WITH BOTH BM'S OBSCURED BY BUSHES. WHEN THE TRANSFERRED DWL ELEVATIONS WERE EDITED TO THE CORRECT BENCHMARK, EHSN REQUIRED RE-ENTRY OF EACH DWL READING BEFORE RECALCULATING THE CORRECT WATER LEVEL. I ADDED 0.2M TO EACH DWL IN ERROR, SO THE CORRECT DWL READING YESTERDAY SHOULD HAVE BEEN 0.022M, NOT 0.222M. THE DWL TODAY WAS RUN FROM THE HOLDING BENCHMARK, WITH A DWL OF 0.016M, TAKEN FROM THE SAME RP1, INDICATING THE WL DROPPED SLIGHTLY OVERNIGHT. THIS IS IN LINE WITH THE LOGGER READINGS, SO AN OFFSET OF 0.2M WILL NEED TO BE APPLIED BACK TO YESTERDAY'S VISIT. Mid-section
